item.summary: Fabric - issue with external git repo and provisioning

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: For the records, I have seen the same NPE in a fabric:create command on 6.2.1 GA when pointing to an external git repo. Could not reproduce it locally though. Error and call stack are identical, so I think it may be the same bug.

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
You need an sshd server that will host a git repo and 2 remote nodes .

0. create a git repo on the sshd node

mkdir /home/fuse/repo
 
cd  /home/fuse/repo
 
git init
 
git config --bool core.bare true

1. from both your node A and node B, connect via shell to the sshd node with the same user that will run fuse, this is required so that ssh configuration will "know" the remote server and it won't block expecting fuse to accept the fingerprint.

2. configure both nodes A and B with the correct external git repo config:

printf '\n\ngitRemoteUrl=ssh://fuse@172.17.0.4/home/fuse/repo\ngitRemoteUser=fuse' >> etc/io.fabric8.datastore.cfg

3. Start node A and create a Fabric:

fabric:create --wait-for-provisioning --external-git-url ssh://fuse@172.17.0.4/home/fuse/repo --external-git-user fuse --zookeeper-password paolo  --resolver localip

4. From node B, join the Fabric:

fabric:join  --resolver localip   --zookeeper-password paolo  172.17.0.2:2181 node1

Opertion will apparently succeed, but you will see errors in node B logs, and Node B will never reach the SUCCESS status in container-list output
